<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,824]" box="[199,964,727,752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,727,752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Distribution.</emphasis>
From southern South America to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[871,961,727,752]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<collectingRegion box="[871,961,727,752]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Mexico</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,390,764,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Natural history.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[524,636,764,788]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Apopyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,636,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Apopyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in areas with rocky ground and, at least 
<emphasis box="[1255,1364,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1360,764,788]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Apopyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suavis">A. suavis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
might be active during daylight (GHFA personal observation).
</paragraph>
